    {
      "type": 1,
      "content": {
        "json": "---\n### \ud83d\udd0d Next steps when a candidate is identified\n1. **Click the database name** \u2192 Metrics blade \u2192 extend time range to 30\u201390 days\n2. **Check Query Store** in the portal (SQL DB blade \u2192 Query Performance Insight) for actual query activity\n3. **Check backup history** \u2014 last restore point date indicates last write activity\n4. For definitive proof of idle: connect and run `SELECT * FROM sys.dm_exec_sessions` or query `sys.dm_db_log_stats` for last log write\n\n*Metrics-only dashboard \u2014 no Log Analytics required. All data from Azure Platform Metrics and Azure Resource Graph (free tier).*"
      },
